{
  "texts": [
    "In the other direction, h p (x) ⊑ ′ y ′ implies h(h p (x)) ⊑ h(y ′), which with (c) implies x ⊑ h(y ′).",
    "(e) h p (f i (x)) = f ′ i (h p (x)), where f i and f ′ i are the left adjoints of ■ i and ■ ′ i, respectively, which exist since A and A ′ are CV-BAOs and hence CT -BAOs (Fact 5.2).",
    "By (d),h p (f i (x)) ⊑ ′ y ′ iff f i (x) ⊑ h(y ′).",
    "Since f i is the left adjoint of ■ i, the right side of the 'iff' is equivalent to x ⊑ ■ i h(y ′) = h(■ ′ i y ′), which by (d) is equivalent to h p (x) ⊑ ′ ■ ′ i y ′, which by the fact that f ′ i is the left adjoint of ■ ′ i is equivalent to f ′ i (h p (x)) ⊑ ′ y ′.",
    "Thus, for any y ′ ∈ A ′ p, h p (f i (x)) ⊑ ′ y ′ iff f ′ i (h p (x)) ⊑ ′ y ′, so h p (f i (x)) = f ′ i (h p (x)).Observation (a) shows that h p satisfies ⊑-forth."
  ]
}